# Supplementary Materials

This directory contains the supplementary materials referenced throughout
the paper, submitted alongside the manuscript.

| File | Referenced in paper | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `A_theorem1_proof.pdf` | Section 3.3, Theorem 1 | Full proof verifying conditions RC1-RC3 for the Ethical-POMDP, completing the instantiation of Paternain et al. [29] |
| `B_gpt4o_prompts/` | Section 5.1 | Complete system prompts and raw outputs for the B1/B2 GPT-4o baselines (snapshot `gpt-4o-2024-08-06`), released for reproducibility given that commercial endpoints evolve over time |
| `C_table_S3_task_completion.csv` | Section 5.1 | Task-completion-only comparison (disjoint from the engagement reward signal), addressing the partial circularity between R_engage and UES |
| `D_confusion_matrix.csv` | Section 4.3 | Confusion matrix for the demographic-inference head across the five cohorts (balanced accuracy 0.78, per-cohort range 0.71-0.84) |
| `S4_s2_subcondition.csv` | Section 5.3 | S2 latency-sensitive sub-condition results, where B5 marginally outperforms MEIA on raw task-completion |

## Notes

- All supplementary CSV/JSON files use the same schema as the corresponding
  `results/raw_logs/` files for direct comparison.
- The Theorem 1 proof (Appendix A) is provided as a standalone PDF for
  reviewer convenience and is not required to run any code in this
  repository.
- The GPT-4o prompt logs (Appendix B) document the exact prompts used;
  re-running them against the live API may yield different results if
  OpenAI updates the pinned snapshot's underlying weights.
